k", "text_ar": "سِمَاك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~aAmiHu", "text_ar": "الرَّامِحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [thus called for a reason expl. in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rmH", "text_ar": "رمح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v., is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the star Arcturus,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and] is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not of the Mansions of the Moon,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and has not any"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nawo'", "text_ar": "نَوْء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[here meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supposed influence in bringing rain &c."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "];"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is towards the north; the former being towards the south;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and is also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~imaAku Almirozamu", "text_ar": "السِّمَاكُ المِرْزَمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (AZ, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rmH", "text_ar": "رمح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) [it is erroneously said that]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "smAkAn", "text_ar": "سماكان"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "are in the sign of Libra:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) and it is said that"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "they are the two kind legs of Leo"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rijolaA AlA^asadi", "text_ar": "رِجْلَا الاَسَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): (S, O, K: *) [for it appears, as I have before observed, (voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*iraAEN", "text_ar": "ذِرَاعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) that the ancient Arabs, or many of them, extended the figure of Leo (as they did"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1431}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also that of Scorpio) far beyond the limits which we assign to it: and hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlsmAk AlA Ezl", "text_ar": "السماك الا عزل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "was also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAqu AlA^asadi", "text_ar": "سَاقُ الاَسَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the thigh,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the hind shank, of Leo"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Kzw in his descr. of Virgo.) The rhyming-proser says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_i*aA TalaEa Als~imaAko *ahaba", "text_ar": "اـِذَا طَلَعَ السِّمَاكْ ذَهَبَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEikaAko faA^aSoliHo finaAko waA^ajid~a Hi*aAko faA_in~a Al$~itaA='a qado A^ataAko", "text_ar": "العِكَاكْ فَاَصْلِحْ فِنَاكْ وَاَجِدَّ حِذَاكْ فَاـِنَّ الشِّتَا=ءَ قَدْ اَتَاكْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "When"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlsmAk", "text_ar": "السماك"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rises aurorally,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlsmAk AlA Ezl", "text_ar": "السماك الا عزل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the sultriness has gone, therefore do thou put thy court,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "yard, in good condition, and renew thy sandal, for the winter has come to thee:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "finaAk", "text_ar": "فِنَاك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hi*aAk", "text_ar": "حِذَاك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being contractions of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "finaA='ak", "text_ar": "فِنَا=ءَك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hi*aA='ak", "text_ar": "حِذَا=ءَك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for the sake of the rhyme]. (O, TA.) The"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nawo'", "text_ar": "نَوْء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[here app. meaning the rain consequent upon the auroral setting] of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlsmAk AlAEzl", "text_ar": "السماك الاعزل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[about the 4th of April, O. S. in Central Arabia] is abundant, but disapproved, because it gives growth to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "na$or", "text_ar": "نَشْر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.], which diseases the camels that pasture upon it. (Kzw in his descr. of the Mansions of the Moon.) [The epithet ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "simaAkiY~N", "text_ar": "سِمَاكِىٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied to the rain above mentioned.] ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~imaAku", "text_ar": "السِّمَاكُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies, (K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "simaAku Alt~aroquwapi", "text_ar": "سِمَاكُ التَّرْقُوَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Ibn-'Abbád, O,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The upper part of the chest, next to the collar-bone."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ibn-'Abbád, O, K.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "S", "O", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n20761", "headword_ar": "سَمَّاكٌ", "root": "smk", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A fishmonger."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MA.)"}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}